Understand dataset
clean/impute missing values
Dive into each attribute
Record observations and create a clean data for model building

Observations and next steps:¶


1. Column Term is categorical because of the usuage "month". It would be good to convert it to numeric as values 36, 60 have different weightage.
2. emp_length impute 'n/a' to '0 year'.
3. mths_since_last_delinq has missing values. These are never delinquent records, we can mark NANs to 0.
4. mths_since_last_record has too many missing values. We will mark NANs to 0 and observe the data.
5. revol_util has %. This needs to be removed and column has to be converted to numeric.
6. issue_d does not provide year of issue. This column would be incorrect to use. We can drop the column.
7. earliest_cr_line moves inconsistently form mm-yy to dd-mm values. We will look at more records and decide to delete.
8. dti is missing 2 values. We can impute mean values.
9. delinq_2yrs,pub_rec_bankruptcies,open_acc,pub_rec,total_acc,inq_last_6mths We will mark NANs to 0.
10.revol_util these are missing values. We will impute mean values.
11.annual_inc these are missing values. We will impute mean values.
Note: All numeric values after imputing will have to recasted to type numeric.

The above observations are going to be executed step-by-step to complete data cleaning.

# Compute the correlation matrix
sns.set(style="white")

# Compute the correlation matrix
corr = df.corr()

# Generate a mask for the upper triangle
mask = np.zeros_like(corr, dtype=np.bool)
mask[np.triu_indices_from(mask)] = True

# Set up the matplotlib figure
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 13))

# Generate a custom diverging colormap
cmap = sns.diverging_palette(220, 10, as_cmap=True)

# Draw the heatmap with the mask and correct aspect ratio

            square=True, linewidths=.5, cbar_kws={"shrink": .5})

Observations:¶


1. Data for charged off is much less than fully paid.
2. Most purpose of the loan is for debt consolidation or credit card, while wedding, renewable energy and education are least reasons to get take loan.
3. Number of loans in California is hightest, almost twice the next highest Florida.
4. There are fewer home owners to take a loan than those on Rent or having home loan.

Loan amount - In-depth analysis¶

Let us look at how loan amount is impacting other variables

Understanding violin plots:¶

  1. At the stomach of the violin is the box plot that gives median value for that category.
  2. The spread is the kernal density distribution, number of data values in that range. a peak can be understood as high concentration of data and narrow representa low number of data.
  3. overall violin gives the range of data in that category.
